File: Gautrain, wage negotiations reached a deadlock after Numsa rejected the company's offer for a 4.1% increase and benefits. JOHANNESBURG - Gautrain workers affiliated with the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) will down tools over wages on Monday. According to a statement from Gautrain, wage negotiations reached a deadlock after Numsa rejected the company's offer for a 4.1% increase and benefits. The union is said to be demanding around 26% percent. Contingency plans were made to ensure train service continues, while additional security will be deployed.